sub_title: MSc in Health Education and Promotion | Business engineer at Netherlands Enterprise Agency (RVO)
summary:
In the Netherlands, we have more CEOs named Peter than female CEOs. Low educated people have a lower life expectancy than those with a higher education. And people with a low social economic status tend to live shorter than people with a high social economic status. There are still too much inequalities in the Netherlands, and that has to change! I am committed to make our society a better place.
I enjoy learning new things or focussing completely on a challenging project, so that I keep expanding my knowledge and skills.

Helping people often starts with providing them with the right information. This has caused my love for education. During my bachelor, I helped secondary school students decide on a bachelor programme by educating them about their options and about student life in general. Furthermore, I have enjoyed working at ‘De Ontdekfabriek’ (discovery factory), where I gave multiple workshops and explained the mechanisms behind them.

In my spare time, I enjoying playing board games or solving escape rooms. I always go all in, so I also participate in national championships related to these hobbies. Additionally, I like to organise events myself. I organise a summer camp on a yearly basis, but I have also organised several student galas, as well as bachelor open days at my university.

Can I help you with anything? Or do you think you might be able to help me? I am always available for a (digital) cup of coffee, so do not hesitate to contact me!

E-mail: inge_sinot@hotmail.com
